<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-486-590  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 486 590.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  May 21 1990 v12 n21 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Controller cards for SCSI drives offered. (Small Computer SystemsInterface) (Distributed Processing Technology's Smartconnex/EISAand Smartconnex/ISA) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brownstein, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Distributed Processing Technology announces two controller boardsthat take full advantage of the capabilities of the new SmallComputer Systems Interface (SCSI) hard drives.andP;  The $715Smartconnex/EISA and the $330 Smartconnex/ISA operate in emulationand enhanced modes.andP;  The emulation mode controls up to two SCSIhard drives and automatically determines the make and model of thedrives and set up system CMOS to correctly address the drives.andO;The enhanced mode provides significant performance improvementsand supports up to seven SCSI devices: hard drives, CD ROM drives,scanners or other SCSI devices.andP;  The ISA version is a 16-bit SCSIcontroller with data transfer rates of 4Mbytes per second.andP;  TheEISA version provides enhanced capabilities and a special busmaster interface controller that allows attached devices tooperate as bus-mastering devices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Distributed Processing Technology Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Distributed Processing Technology SmartConnex/ISA (Peripheralcontroller) (product introduction)Distributed Processing Technology SmartConnex/EISA (Peripheralcontroller) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Small Computer Systems InterfacePeripheral ControllersBoards-CardsProduct Introduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>